headline.main: 51 Japanese Planes Raid Darwin; Take 'Heavy' Toll of Allied Airmen; 51 ENEMY PLANES STRIKE AT DARWIN

lead_paragraph: ALLIED HEADQUARTERS IN AUSTRALIA, Monday, May 3 -- Japanese planes, renewing large-scale attacks on Allied bases in the Southwest Pacific after a two-week lull, attacked Port Darwin, in Northern Australia, yesterday morning and inflicted heavy losses on Allied air defenders.
